Task: Find all TODO comments in the React project and update them with owner and priority information.

Expected changes:
1. Update TODOs to include owner in parentheses
2. Add priority level to each TODO
3. Maintain consistent format across all files

Example format:
// TODO(owner): Description - PRIORITY: level

Solution steps:
1. :vimgrep /TODO\|todo/j **/*.{js,jsx} to find all TODO comments (case insensitive)
2. :copen to open the quickfix window
3. Review TODOs with :cnext and :cprev
4. :cdo s/TODO:/TODO(owner):/ | s/$/ - PRIORITY: medium/ to update format

Alternative approaches:
- Use :args **/*.{js,jsx} then :argdo %s/TODO:/TODO(owner):/ | %s/\(TODO.*\)$/\1 - PRIORITY: medium/
- Use :grep -i "todo" . --include="*.{js,jsx}" for initial search 